caption.text:
"YOU'RE FAT" they said... When I did this shoot 4 years ago, a lot of people kept telling me that I had to loose weight, otherwise I would never work as an actress... And that's how I ended up getting a CHRONIC disease... I was hating myself so much, just because I gave credit to people who had the power to make my dream come true... and one day, my body said STOP!!! Today as I am practically recovered (Yayyy!üòä), I look at this picture and I think "What an IDIOT I am!!!". I was not FAT at all!!! And EVEN if I was??!!!! I spend 2 years recovering, doing blood tests, taking pills which made me lose my hair, my memory, I couldn't even remember the movie we saw!!! I couldn't even stand up and be normal. And stay awake.

It's been tough and it ruined many things just because I wasn't able to have a normal life... I ended up loosing people I truly love... and today I would do anything I could to repair that, and show them who I really am, the real "me". Anyway, it's time to SERIOUSLY change the belief that you have to fit some physical criteria to succeed the business! NO MATTER WHAT you look like, who you are, no matter how big, how thin, how tall, small, old, young, blond or brown you are... Don't let ANYONE tell you that you aren't good enough... that you won't make it! This is your life, your body, and only you have the power to decide what you're going to be!
